<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-12-1107 </DOCNO><TEXT>Using as an example the formation and reduction of nitric oxides, thepaper discusses possible ways of studying and influencing the formationof NO/sub x/ by analysing the chemical elementary stages which occur.By applying various contactless laser-spectroscope diagnostic methods(laser-induced fluorescence; coherent anti-Stokes Raman spectroscopy;multi-photon ionisation spectroscopy) it is possible to carry out a separatequantitative investigation of the individual elementary stages. Mathematicalmodelling of microscopic chemical kinetics of selective NO reductionis described as a basis of a regulating system for the optimal controlof NO/sub x/ emissions with changing waste-gas compositions.</TEXT></DOC>